<TITLE> 44 die as Kishoreganj boat sinks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoregonj, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)At least 44 people died and scores were missing on Friday after a boat capsized on the Daira river at Mithamoin in Bhairab. Kishoregonj deputy commissioner Mohammad Shah Alam told bdnews24.com the accident took place at around 9:30am when a Bhairab-bound engine boat collided head-on with passenger ferry MV Al-Helal near Charigram in Mithamoin upazila. Some 50 boat passengers went under water. The dead could not be immediately identified, Alam said. He said at 2:30pm that 44 bodies have been recovered. A survivor of the boat, Jasimuddin, said the boat was carrying around 100 passengers to Karimganj from Kadamchhal village of Ashtogram upazila. Local people have been carrying out rescue operations since morning. Divers from Dhaka are yet to reach the spot, he added. A ferry, MV Coco-4, partially capsized last Friday, the night before Eid-ul-Azha, at Nazirpur river station in Lalmohan, some 40 km from Bhola district town, killing 85 people and leaving many missing. The vessel, crowded from hull to decks with people heading home to celebrate the holiday with families, began tipping with the weight of disembarking passengers and partially sank. bdnews2
